<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About — The Inkwell Ledger</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,300;0,9..144,400;0,9..144,600;1,9..144,300;1,9..144,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&family=Lato:wght@300;400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('layouts/nav') %>
  <main>
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <p class="about-label">About this place</p>
        <h1 class="about-title">The Inkwell Ledger</h1>
        <div class="about-body prose">
          <p>This is a personal blog built as a portfolio project demonstrating full-stack web development with Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, EJS, and React.</p>
          <p>The stack is deliberately close to the metal — raw SQL, hand-written middleware, server-rendered EJS for public pages, and a React-powered CMS admin panel.</p>
          <h2>The Stack</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Node.js + Express</strong> — HTTP server and routing</li>
            <li><strong>PostgreSQL</strong> — relational database with raw SQL queries</li>
            <li><strong>EJS</strong> — server-side rendered templates for public pages</li>
            <li><strong>React + Tiptap</strong> — rich text editor in the admin CMS</li>
            <li><strong>OAuth 2.0</strong> — Google & GitHub sign-in via Passport.js</li>
            <li><strong>Cloudinary</strong> — image upload and CDN delivery</li>
          </ul>
          <h2>Features</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Full CRUD for posts, tags, and comments</li>
            <li>Draft / Published / Archived publishing workflow</li>
            <li>Comment moderation queue</li>
            <li>Role-based access control (admin vs. reader)</li>
            <li>Parameterized SQL queries (no ORM, no injection)</li>
            <li>Session persistence in PostgreSQL</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn--primary" style="margin-top:2rem;">Read the writing →</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <%- include('layouts/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
